sdate.1: Escape tilde character

The tilde (~) character in groff input produces a "modifier tilde"
in the output. Use the \(ti escape sequence for a normal tilde,
see groff_char(7).

commit.message:
Send error messages to stderr + provide usage information on stdout

Error messages should go to stderr, while usage information
should go to stdout if it was explicitly requested (via -h/--help).

commit.message:
Add alternative COVID mode

Implement a COVID mode, enabled via new -c/--covid option with a mandatory
variant specfication. This mode sets epoch to an appropriate value for the
specific COVID variant. Also add initial support for variant 19, in order
to enable displaying the never ending March date.

Signed-off-by: Leif Lindholm <leif@eciton.net>
Use DH 12 and strip down rules to the minimum.

Remove fake library

Not needed anymore (if ever)
